### 🐛 Current behavior

The `__isArtificial` flag in `<NoResultsBoundary>` component (copied from the [documentation](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/going-further/conditional-display/react/#display-a-message)
Shows UI hydration error on Next.js (App router).

When logging the `results` object from `useInstantSearch` by `console.log()` command, I've noticed the missing `__isArtificial` key on the client-side that may cause inconsistency between client-side and server-side rendering:

